#I choose the Lotka-Volterra competition model to simulate the interactions between species. In this project, the model tracks how oral bacteria complete for nutrients and space. 
The method lotka_volterra has the parameters of current population sizes of bacterial species (N), simulated time (t), bacterial growth rates (r), and interaction matrix describing competition between species (A). 
dNdt = N * (r + A @N) formula calculated how populations change over time.
R-increases population growth 
A @ N-how bacteria affect one another through competition 

# -The r variable gives each bacterial species a different growth speed, and the np.fill_diagonal method represents self-limitation: when a bacterial population becomes too large, its own growth slows down, which corresponds with ecology aspect of this model. 
-The trajectory is for the generation of the graph, which helps to import into Blender later. 
-The reason why the code can simulate the changes over time is that the dataset has data for each species’ samples, information and patient samples. 

